===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|steem|lang=enm}}, {{term|stem|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|stēam||steam, hot exhalation, hot breath; that which emits vapour; blood}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*staumaz||steam, vapour, breath}}, from {{etyl|thanks and have fun e-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*dʰew-||to whirl, waft, stink, shake; steam, haze, smoke}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|stem|lang=sco}}, {{term|steam||steam|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|steam||steam, vapour|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|stoom||steam, vapour|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|stom||steam|lang=nds}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} dialectal {{term|stimma||steam, fog|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{m|la|fūmus||smoke, steam}}.

